{"lemma":"قِبْطِيٌّ","slug":"قِبْطِيٌّ","root":"ق.ب.ط","root_slug":"ق-ب-ط","root_link":"/words/roots/ق-ب-ط","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n35118","n35119"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%82%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B7%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8C%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"Coptic"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"Egyptian","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Copt"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"Egyptian","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"قِبْط (qibṭ, “Copts”) + ـِيّ (-iyy)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n35118","headword_ar":"قُبْطِىٌّ","root":"qbT","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A kind of thin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fine,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cloth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of linen,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made in Egypt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called in relation to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiboT","text_ar":"قِبْط"},{"kind":"text","text":", irregularly, to distinguish between it and the man, who is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiboTiY~N","text_ar":"قِبْطِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh, Msb:) so says Lth, respecting these two forms: (TA:) you also say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"viyaAbN qiboTiy~apN","text_ar":"ثِيَابٌ قِبْطِيَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr; but when you convert the rel. n. into a subst, you say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quboTiy~apN","text_ar":"قُبْطِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, to distinguish the subst. from the rel. n. without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vyAb","text_ar":"ثياب"},{"kind":"text","text":"; like as you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rimaAHN xaT~iy~apN","text_ar":"رِمَاحٌ خَطِّيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xiT~iy~apN","text_ar":"خِطِّيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr, when you do not mention the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rmAH","text_ar":"رماح"},{"kind":"text","text":": so says Kh: (Msb in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xT","text_ar":"خط"},{"kind":"text","text":":) it is said in the K, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlquboTiy~apu","text_ar":"القُبْطِيَّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with damm, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of cloths,"},{"kind":"text","text":"so called in relation to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiboT","text_ar":"قِبْط"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and sometimes it is with kesr; which is a plain assertion that the form with damm is the more common: but in the S it is said, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqiboTiy~ipu","text_ar":"القِبْطِيِّةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"certain white, thin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fine, cloths, of linen, made in Egypt;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes it is with damm, because they make a change in the rel. n., as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"suholiY~N","text_ar":"سُهْلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duhoriY~N","text_ar":"دُهْرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which (as SM adds) are from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saholN","text_ar":"سَهْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dahorN","text_ar":"دَهْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and this indicates that the regular form, with kesr, is the more common: (TA:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaATiY~N","text_ar":"قَبَاطِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaATiY","text_ar":"قَبَاطِى"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K [but the latter, being indeterminate, should be written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaATK","text_ar":"قَبَاطٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mahaArK","text_ar":"مَهَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.:]) Sh says, that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qabaATiY~","text_ar":"قَبَاطِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of cloths inclining to fineness and thinness and whiteness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","TA","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n35119","headword_ar":"قِبْطِىٌّ","root":"qbT","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qiboTiy~apN","text_ar":"قِبْطِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqiboTu","text_ar":"القِبْطُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quboTiY~N","text_ar":"قُبْطِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}